Package: lambda
Title: Simple anonymous functions
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Jim", "Hester", email = "james.f.hester@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Defines a function 'f()' to create anonymous functions (lambdas)
  in a very concise manner. Simply write the body of the function as you would
  normally.  If you want a given variable to appear as one of the arguments to
  the function, put it in '.()'.
Depends: R (>= 3.3.0)
License: MIT
LazyData: true
